#!/bin/sh
#
# PGSD Welcome Script
# Displays welcome information for the live environment
#

cat <<'EOF'

╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                                                                      ║
║                    Welcome to PGSD Live Environment!                 ║
║                                                                      ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

This is a live boot environment for installing PGSD on your system.

QUICK START:
-----------
  To install PGSD on your hard drive:
    $ sudo pgsd-install

  Or run the installer directly:
    $ sudo pgsd-inst

NETWORK SETUP:
-------------
  WiFi configuration:
    $ sudo wpa_passphrase "SSID" "password" >> /etc/wpa_supplicant.conf
    $ sudo service wpa_supplicant restart
    $ sudo service dhcpcd restart

  Wired (automatic DHCP):
    Should work automatically via dhcpcd

SYSTEM INFORMATION:
------------------
  • OS: FreeBSD with PGSD customizations
  • Display Server: Arcan
  • Window Manager: Durden
  • Default Shell: ZSH

USEFUL COMMANDS:
---------------
  pgsd-install        Launch the installer (requires root)
  pgsd-inst           Direct installer binary (requires root)
  beadm list          List available images (after installation)
  diskinfo -v         Show disk information
  gpart show          Display partition table
  zpool status        Show ZFS pool status (after installation)

KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS (Durden):
---------------------------
  Meta + Enter        Open terminal (foot)
  Meta + D            Application launcher
  Meta + Shift + Q    Close window
  Meta + F            Toggle fullscreen
  Meta + Arrow Keys   Switch workspaces

  (Meta key is typically the Windows/Super key)

GETTING HELP:
------------
  • Documentation: /usr/local/share/pgsd/README.txt
  • Arcan Documentation: https://arcan-fe.com
  • FreeBSD Handbook: https://docs.freebsd.org

TROUBLESHOOTING:
---------------
  If Arcan/Durden doesn't start:
    $ startx           (alternative, if X11 is available)
    $ arcan durden     (manual Arcan start)

  Check system logs:
    $ dmesg | less
    $ tail -f /var/log/messages

  Network issues:
    $ ifconfig         (list network interfaces)
    $ service netif restart

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

EOF
